1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:11,586
The clock on the wall has secrets we can't
speak,

2
00:00:11,736 --> 00:00:18,323
Its hands are misplaced, its numbers
antique.

3
00:00:18,473 --> 00:00:25,059
We glance at the ceiling, we stare at the
floor,

4
00:00:25,209 --> 00:00:31,795
Time’s just a rumor we heard once before.

5
00:00:31,945 --> 00:00:38,532
If no one can read it, does the second
even hit?

6
00:00:38,682 --> 00:00:45,268
We’re checking our screens like they’re
telling us truth.

7
00:00:45,418 --> 00:00:52,004
Maybe time’s just a game that we can’t
really quit,

8
00:00:52,154 --> 00:00:58,741
And we’re lost in the halls, just trying
to fit.

9
00:00:58,891 --> 00:01:05,477
The classroom’s a forest, and clocks are
the trees,

10
00:01:05,627 --> 00:01:12,213
They fall every second, but no one
believes.

11
00:01:12,363 --> 00:01:18,950
We borrow the time from a digital friend,

12
00:01:19,100 --> 00:01:25,686
But what if the moments have no start or
end?

13
00:01:25,836 --> 00:01:32,422
If no one can read it, does the second
even hit?

14
00:01:32,572 --> 00:01:39,159
We’re checking our screens like they’re
telling us truth.

15
00:01:39,309 --> 00:01:45,895
Maybe time’s just a game that we can’t
really quit,

16
00:01:46,045 --> 00:01:52,631
And we’re lost in the halls, just trying
to fit.

17
00:01:52,781 --> 00:01:59,368
So we stare at the ticking of clocks we
can’t know,

18
00:01:59,518 --> 00:02:06,104
We’re never too early, we’re never too
slow.

19
00:02:06,254 --> 00:02:12,840
The past is a myth and the future’s a
haze,

20
00:02:12,990 --> 00:02:19,577
We’re stuck in this infinite maze.

21
00:02:19,727 --> 00:02:26,313
If no one can read it, does the second
even hit?

22
00:02:26,463 --> 00:02:33,049
We’re checking our screens like they’re
telling us truth.

23
00:02:33,199 --> 00:02:39,786
Maybe time’s just a game that we can’t
really quit,

24
00:02:39,936 --> 00:02:46,522
And we’re lost in the halls, just trying
to fit.
